{
  "id": "the-bee-and-jupiter",
  "title": "The Bee and Jupiter",
  "subtitle": "Aesop's Fables, Volume 02",
  "level": "A2-B1",
  "duration": 71.2,
  "audioFileName": "the-bee-and-jupiter.mp3",
  "sourceURL": "https://librivox.org/aesops-fables-volume-2-fables-26-50/",
  "textSourceURL": "https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/11339",
  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 16.1,
      "end": 16.58,
      "text": "A",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 23.44,
      "end": 28.12,
      "text": "Queen B from Hymetis flew up to Olympus with some fresh honey from the hive as a present",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 28.12,
      "end": 32.36,
      "text": "to Jupiter, who was so pleased with the gift that he promised to give her anything she",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 32.36,
      "end": 33.16,
      "text": "liked to ask for.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 34.1,
      "end": 38.32,
      "text": "She said she would be very grateful if he would give stings to the bees to kill people who",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 38.32,
      "end": 39.22,
      "text": "robbed them of their honey.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 39.92,
      "end": 45.0,
      "text": "Jupiter was greatly displeased with this request, for he loved mankind, but he had given his",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 45.0,
      "end": 51.24,
      "text": "word, so he said that stings they should have, the stings he gave them, however, were of",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 51.24,
      "end": 55.84,
      "text": "such a kind that whenever a bee stings a man, the sting is left in the wound and the bee",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 55.84,
      "end": 56.42,
      "text": "dies.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 58.16,
      "end": 61.08,
      "text": "Evil wishes like fouls come home to roost.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 62.02,
      "end": 64.32,
      "text": "End of the Bee and Jupiter.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 65.4,
      "end": 71.22,
      "text": "Recorded on January 24, 2006, in Newmarket, Ontario, Canada.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
